article.headline: Nicholls State 86, Texas State 67
article.story: THIBODAUX, La. (AP) -- Stefan Blaszczynski scored 25 points and two other players also broke the 20-point mark as Nicholls State defeated Texas State 86-67 Friday. Cyril Djoukeng added 23 points for the Colonels (9-18, 5-11 Southland) and Adonis Gray had 20. Blaszczynski was 10-of-14 from the field, 3-of-5 from 3-point range and 2-of-2 from the free-throw line. Djoukeng was a perfect 6-of-6 from the free-throw line. James Dixon also added 10 points for Nicholls. Brandon Bush led Texas State (3-24, 1-15) with 21 points. Charles Dotson added 12 and Lance Burroughs had 10. The Colonels led 38-28 at the half.
